author: Andrew Mark Miller
title: Chelsea Clinton’s New Book Is No. 74,374 On Amazon Bestseller’s List
text:
10:52pm February 14, 2017   
Now that Hillary and Bill are finally out of the picture it seems like a lot of attention has been shifted to Hillary Clinton. 
The left is trying to get her to run for public office showing once again how tone deaf they are. 
However, we might be jumping the gun a little bit when it comes to judging Chelsea’s likability. 
Check out the clear message that Americans sent her when she released her last book. 
From Heat Street : 
Last week a new book was published co-written by Chelsea Clinton and entitled Governing Global Health: Who Runs the World and Why? Almost no one is buying the Clinton title, co-authored by Devi Sridhar, a Global Public Health Professor at the University of Edinburgh. It currently stands at No. 74,374 on the Amazon Bestsellers Chart. Weirdly, Chelsea Clinton herself appears disinterested in promoting her book. Her Twitter bio only mentions her children’s book It’s Your World (which is higher on Amazon’s charts than the new work). Not exactly the most popular author in the world… Hillary wasn’t likable. At all. It’s starting to look like Chelsea might have the same problem. LIKE this article? I hated this article. I'm a liberal.
